nings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"WILLIAM CRIKETOT was born in 1139, in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter. He died in 1269, at the age of 130."},"et":{"1139–1269":"1139–1269","1259–1293":"1259–1293","1139":"1139","1259":"1259","1269":"1269","1293":"1293","Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1139–1269":"1139–1269","1259–1293":"1259–1293","1139":"1139","1259":"1259","1269":"1269","1293":"1293","Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1139–1269":"1139–1269","1259–1293":"1259–1293","1139":"1139","1259":"1259","1269":"1269","1293":"1293","Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"WILLIAM CRIKETOT est né en 1139, à Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1269, à l’âge de 130 ans."},"de":{"1139–1269":"1139–1269","1259–1293":"1259–1293","1139":"1139","1259":"1259","1269":"1269","1293":"1293","Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"WILLIAM CRIKETOT wurde 1139 in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Tochter. Er starb 1269 im Alter von 130 Jahren."},"ht":{"1139–1269":"1139–1269","1259–1293":"1259–1293","1139":"1139","1259":"1259","1269":"1269","1293":"1293","Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, A